# Deploy on "PUSH" / "push"

When the user says **only** `PUSH`, `push`, or clearly means deploy now:

```bash
cd "{{LOCAL_FOLDER_PATH}}"
git add .
git commit -m "Test auto deployment"
git push
```

- No secrets in commits; no empty commits; no force-push unless requested.
- User provides a message → use their message.

After push: commit hash, `origin/main`, https://{{CANONICAL_HOST}}
